# No em dashes

Do not use the em dash character (`—`, U+2014) anywhere in this project: UI copy, content files, alt text, comments meant for users, or metadata.

Use instead:
- a comma for light pauses or lists (`hours, plus settings`)
- a period for separate sentences
- a hyphen `-` only for compound words or ranges (e.g. `local-first`, `25-min`)

Before finishing copy edits, search the changed files for `—` and remove any matches.
